    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The Spokane socialists have\npassed resolutions denouncing\nRoosevelt for sending troops to\nGoldfield. The action is called\n\"perfidious and reasonable to the\nbest interests Of the working class\"\nand the socialists call upon all\nworking men to arouse themselves\nto their duty and make their wish\nes respected by casting a solid\nballot against all capitalist parties,\nand in future to elect men of their\nown class to make and execute the\nlaws\"\n\n\nThe resolutions recite that the\ntroops were sent to Goldfield to aid\nthe mine owners to disrupt the\nminers union and establish the\nopen mine\" system"
    }
  ]
